CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, April 6, 1946, pg. 9, reads: "Throngs Expected at Beauty Shop Owners' Revue - Last Call for Glamour!  April 9 is the date set for the annual Beauty Shop Owners' Association fashion revue at Schenley High School and all the lovely ladies and kiddies above will appear in the the show which promises to be the best yet... Far right: Georgia Cats and Ruth Simpson have just had a stirring game of tennis... - All Photos by Harris."
TitMainTitle: Georgia Cats and Ruth Simpson holding tennis rackets and posed next to blossoming tree, possibly Schenley Park
